author: The Current
description:
Watch Soul Asylum's acoustic performance of "Misery" at The Current
Support The Current: https://support.mpr.org/youtube or hit the Thanks button

Longtime Minneapolis rock band Soul Asylum visited The Current for an acoustic set and a conversation with host Mac Wilson. Here are Soul Asylum playing an acoustic version of the song "Misery" from their 1995 album, "Let Your Dim Light Shine."

Musicians
David Pirner – lead vocals, guitar
Ryan Smith – lead guitar
Jeremy Tappero – bass

Credits

Host – Mac Wilson
Producer – Derrick Stevens
Video – Megan Lundberg, Eric Xu Romani, Will Keeler
Audio – Evan Clark

author: The Current
description:
Watch Hayes Carll perform "Progress of Man (Bitcoin & Cattle)" in studio
Support The Current: https://support.mpr.org/youtube or hit the Thanks button

Texas singer-songwriter Hayes Carll released his 10th album, "We’re Only Human," on August 8. While on tour in support of the album, Carll visited The Current to play songs from the new record and to catch up with host Bill DeVille. 

Watch and listen to a performance of "Progress of Man (Bitcoin & Cattle)" above.

Musicians
Hayes Carll - guitar, vocals
Noah Jeffries - fiddle, mandolin

Credits
Guest – @hayescarll 
Host – Bill DeVille
Producers – Bill DeVille, Mike Pengra
Video – Josh Sauvageau
Audio – Evan Clark
